    {
        "content": "<p>I believe the statement in Borceux is incorrect: being pointwise epic is sufficient, but not necessary. The question of the induced functor being fully faithful is the topic of Karazeris–Velebil's <a href=\"http://www.tac.mta.ca/tac/volumes/18/14/18-14abs.html\">Dense morphisms of monads</a>. See Remark 3.5 there in particular.</p>",
        "id": 500947074,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1740077026
    }
]